OL,6,F"A lifebelt was thrown to him but
OL,7,Funfortunately due to exhaustion and
OL,8,Fthe onset of hyperthermia, he was
OL,9,Funable to reach it.
OL,11,F"After a dynamic assessment and
OL,12,Frealising the gravity of the
OL,13,Fsituation, I entered the water from
OL,14,Fthe bow of the Arun class Gough
OL,15,FRitchie and swam to the casualty as he
OL,16,Fwas about to slip below the surface.
OL,18,F"With a hold of the lifering and the
OL,19,Fcasualty, we were then both recovered
OL,20,Fto the safety of the lifeboat."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/7
